WEBVTT

00:39.197 --> 00:40.898
<i>Now,
they're gonna be out there cleaning up</i>

00:40.932 --> 00:42.066
<i>for the next several days,
folks.</i>

00:42.100 --> 00:45.203
<i>The governor has declared
a state of emergency</i>

00:45.236 --> 00:47.105
<i>as we expect heavy flooding
and high winds</i>

00:47.138 --> 00:48.139
<i>throughout the night.</i>

00:48.172 --> 00:50.108
<i>Local authorities
are urging everyone</i>

00:50.141 --> 00:52.511
<i>to stay inside.</i>

00:52.544 --> 00:54.613
<i>For more details on the impact
on the ground,</i>

00:54.646 --> 00:56.914
<i>let's throw it over to Mia
in the newsroom.</i>

00:56.948 --> 00:58.216
- Mia.
- <i>Thank you, Tom.</i>

00:58.249 --> 01:01.285
<i>The National Weather Service
has confirmed a category 3</i>

01:01.319 --> 01:04.456
<i>at landfall with sustained winds
of 100 miles per hour</i>

01:04.489 --> 01:08.159
<i>and gusts up to 130 in some
areas of Jefferies County,</i>

01:08.192 --> 01:10.429
<i>in addition to widespread
power outages.</i>

01:10.462 --> 01:13.131
<i>Emergency services
are expecting extensive damage</i>

01:13.164 --> 01:14.600
<i>over the next eight hours.</i>

01:14.633 --> 01:16.402
<i>And we're getting
reports of closures of parts</i>

01:16.435 --> 01:19.170
<i>of Interstate 84, 95,
and the Merritt.</i>

01:19.203 --> 01:20.171
<i>You know what?</i>

01:20.204 --> 01:23.307
<i>Why don't you just stay
off the roads entirely?</i>

01:28.514 --> 01:30.148
I don't know
how long we're gonna be able

01:30.181 --> 01:31.249
to stay on the air.

01:31.282 --> 01:36.488
Keep yourself safe inside
and just get through the night.

02:02.013 --> 02:02.614
God damn, Jesus Christ!

02:02.648 --> 02:04.182
Come on, close the door.

02:04.215 --> 02:05.183
Get on in here.

02:05.216 --> 02:07.318
Ern, you got the first-aid kit?

02:07.352 --> 02:09.455
What all you do this time?

02:09.488 --> 02:12.123
Tried to swat the motherfucker,
but he disappeared.

02:12.156 --> 02:13.324
Just my luck.

02:13.358 --> 02:15.059
Was it that raccoon again?

02:15.092 --> 02:16.762
That little dumpster bitch!

02:16.795 --> 02:18.330
Well, I don't know,
this thing was flyin'.

02:18.363 --> 02:20.399
- I don't know what it was.
- Flying?

02:20.432 --> 02:21.199
Huh.

02:21.232 --> 02:23.769
That's not good.

02:23.802 --> 02:27.104
God damn.

02:27.138 --> 02:31.108
You should uh... you should
really get that checked out.

02:31.142 --> 02:32.611
If it was flying,
it might've been a...

02:32.644 --> 02:35.012
- I'm fine, I'm fine.
- You feel hot?

02:35.046 --> 02:37.483
- Uh, headachey?
- No, nothing.

02:37.516 --> 02:39.718
'Cause if it was flying,
it might have been a bat.

02:39.751 --> 02:44.255
And if you got bit by a bat,
you could have rabies.

02:52.063 --> 02:55.233
You alright?

02:55.266 --> 02:57.268
I'm not good with these.

02:57.301 --> 02:58.737
Why don't you let me get you
to a doctor?

02:58.770 --> 03:00.606
There's that walk-in
a few miles out.

03:00.639 --> 03:02.641
You know, we couldn't
even if I wanted to.

03:02.674 --> 03:04.643
Tree fell down halfway
up the access road,

03:04.676 --> 03:06.378
it took out
all the streetlights.

03:06.411 --> 03:07.779
I had to walk the rest
of the way here.

03:07.813 --> 03:09.648
I got a big truck.

03:09.681 --> 03:13.117
Whatever it is, it's gonna have
to wait until sunrise.

03:13.150 --> 03:15.119
Never missed a show.

03:15.152 --> 03:17.456
Not gonna start now.

03:17.489 --> 03:19.658
Bob wants to see you
in his office.

03:24.596 --> 03:25.497
He did not.

03:25.531 --> 03:28.333
- You're kidding.
- Hand to God, sweetheart.

03:28.367 --> 03:29.601
Hand to God.

03:29.635 --> 03:31.269
- I can't believe...
- Amazing.

03:31.302 --> 03:32.236
Uh, Amy, come in.

03:32.270 --> 03:33.405
Come in.

03:33.438 --> 03:36.073
Cutting it kind of close,
don't you think?

03:36.107 --> 03:37.275
Have you looked out the window?

03:37.308 --> 03:39.411
Can't say I have.

03:39.444 --> 03:41.547
Got too good a view right here.

03:41.580 --> 03:43.682
Stop it, Robert.

03:43.715 --> 03:46.217
Please, sweetheart,
call me "Bob".

03:46.250 --> 03:47.519
- Bob.
- Robert.

03:47.553 --> 03:50.722
Amy, this is Sienna Walker.

03:50.756 --> 03:53.157
She's from...

03:53.190 --> 03:54.292
UC Berkeley.

03:54.326 --> 03:55.527
I just finished up my Master's

03:55.561 --> 03:58.095
and I came home
to take care of mom.

03:58.129 --> 04:00.197
Um...

04:00.231 --> 04:02.834
I grew up listening to you.

04:02.868 --> 04:05.069
I'm a big fan.

04:06.772 --> 04:08.373
- Nice.
- Yeah.

04:08.407 --> 04:10.742
She's gonna be
your shadow tonight.

04:10.776 --> 04:12.411
Make sure you show her
the ropes.

04:12.444 --> 04:14.211
I... I don't wanna impose, or...

04:14.245 --> 04:15.447
Oh, nonsense.

04:15.480 --> 04:16.781
She'd love to.

04:16.815 --> 04:18.649
I'm sorry, what are you?

04:18.684 --> 04:20.752
Well, I'm coming on as a sub.

04:20.786 --> 04:21.786
Mr. Collins came in on...

04:21.820 --> 04:24.590
- Bob.
- Bob...

04:24.623 --> 04:27.626
Came on Career Day
when I was a senior at Carrigan,

04:27.659 --> 04:30.762
and he gave me his card,
and told me to reach out

04:30.796 --> 04:32.864
when I entered the real world,
so...

04:34.433 --> 04:35.734
Here I am.

04:35.767 --> 04:36.602
Lovely.

04:36.635 --> 04:39.270
Yeah, it really is.

04:39.303 --> 04:40.472
You know, it's a scary time,

04:40.505 --> 04:43.240
so it's just nice
to have somebody there

04:43.274 --> 04:44.409
while you're transitioning.

04:44.443 --> 04:45.577
Well, what can I say?

04:45.611 --> 04:47.512
I've made a career... nay,

04:47.546 --> 04:52.249
a life out of seeing things
in people.

04:52.283 --> 04:54.218
- Like I did with you, Amy.
- Hmm.

04:54.251 --> 04:56.855
It's my gift.

04:58.322 --> 04:59.858
If you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna head

04:59.891 --> 05:01.893
to the ladies' room
freshen up.

05:01.927 --> 05:04.261
Good idea, Amy,
why don't you tag along?

05:04.295 --> 05:05.697
You're looking a touch pale.

05:05.731 --> 05:07.164
That's alright, thanks.

05:07.198 --> 05:08.367
I just have a face for radio.

05:08.400 --> 05:09.334
Oh, stop!

05:09.368 --> 05:10.836
You're beautiful.

05:10.869 --> 05:13.137
And you've got a show
in a few minutes, so...

05:17.274 --> 05:19.544
- You're fucking her.
- Amy!

05:19.578 --> 05:21.278
Oh, come on!

05:21.312 --> 05:22.881
I remember being her age.

05:22.914 --> 05:24.181
Do you?

05:24.215 --> 05:25.249
It was a while ago.

05:25.282 --> 05:26.317
Cut the bullshit.

05:26.351 --> 05:28.487
The fact that you have that
perception of me is fra...

05:28.520 --> 05:30.187
Oh, please, Robert!

05:30.221 --> 05:34.726
Late-night office rendezvous,
brandies, vinyl.

05:34.760 --> 05:37.529
"Call me 'Bob'."

05:37.562 --> 05:38.563
Nothing ever changes with you.

05:38.597 --> 05:40.599
Oh, come on, Amy.

05:40.632 --> 05:43.300
It's all harmless flirtation.

05:43.335 --> 05:47.472
It wasn't then
and it's not now.

05:47.506 --> 05:51.743
You loved it
when it was your turn.

05:51.777 --> 05:54.413
Play nice.

05:54.446 --> 05:56.481
You have a show.

05:58.984 --> 06:01.787
<i>You know,
that's what I like about you, Amy.</i>

06:01.820 --> 06:03.455
<i>You do your shit old school.</i>

06:03.488 --> 06:05.557
When did all this become
old school?

06:05.590 --> 06:06.558
<i>Decade ago.</i>

06:06.591 --> 06:08.593
<i>At least.</i>

06:08.627 --> 06:10.495
Go to hell.

06:12.597 --> 06:13.732
Pickin' up out there, yeah?

06:13.765 --> 06:14.332
Hmm.

06:14.366 --> 06:16.902
Never seen a storm this bad.

06:16.935 --> 06:18.570
We're stuck in here
for the night.

06:18.603 --> 06:19.538
<i>Fine by me.</i>

06:19.571 --> 06:21.573
<i>Got nowhere to be.</i>

06:21.606 --> 06:22.808
What about that girl?

06:22.841 --> 06:23.775
<i>Which one?</i>

06:23.809 --> 06:24.976
The redhead.

06:25.010 --> 06:26.511
Which one?

06:28.346 --> 06:29.381
You just met her!

06:29.414 --> 06:30.782
And she's gone.

06:30.816 --> 06:31.416
Long gone.

06:31.450 --> 06:33.385
They come and they go.

06:33.418 --> 06:36.621
Hey, I just know what I like.

06:39.725 --> 06:41.993
What do we think
of the new chick?

06:42.027 --> 06:43.862
Who you talkin' about?
Bob's new piece of ass?

06:43.895 --> 06:45.731
Somebody else thinks it, too!

06:45.764 --> 06:49.768
I mean, Amy, you gotta be blind
as a bat to not see that shit.

06:49.801 --> 06:51.803
She does have credentials,
though.

06:51.837 --> 06:53.739
Yeah.

06:53.772 --> 06:55.707
But she's no Amy Marlowe.

06:58.610 --> 06:59.745
You alright, Ames?

06:59.778 --> 07:01.913
Mm, I just didn't have dinner
tonight.

07:01.947 --> 07:02.981
You want a bite?

07:03.014 --> 07:04.683
- Garlic noodle.
- Blagh.

07:04.716 --> 07:06.551
Doesn't sit well with me.

07:14.960 --> 07:16.795
Goddammit!

07:22.501 --> 07:24.770
You still got your sweet tooth,
yeah?

07:24.803 --> 07:26.705
You wanna start
with call-ins tonight?

07:26.738 --> 07:28.774
- Call-ins?
- Yeah.

07:28.807 --> 07:30.509
We haven't done that in years.

07:30.542 --> 07:33.745
Thought it might be nice
to revive a classic.

07:35.447 --> 07:36.915
Any reason why?

07:36.948 --> 07:39.818
Always was my
favorite part of the show.

07:39.851 --> 07:43.822
My mom used to play the radio
while I fell asleep

07:43.855 --> 07:45.891
and usually she'd turn it off
once I conked out,

07:45.924 --> 07:49.928
but sometimes she'd forget.

07:49.961 --> 07:54.766
And I'd wake up
and there you were.

07:54.800 --> 07:55.934
You know,
whenever I heard your voice,

07:55.967 --> 08:00.906
I knew it was so far past
my bedtime.

08:00.939 --> 08:04.042
It felt like I was gettin' away
with something.

08:04.075 --> 08:05.610
Why the sudden nostalgia?

08:05.644 --> 08:07.112
You know,
I actually called you once.

08:07.145 --> 08:07.813
- No.
- Yeah.

08:07.846 --> 08:10.448
I must've been
8 or 9 years old.

08:10.482 --> 08:11.550
Topic of discussion...

08:13.084 --> 08:15.120
Dealing with change.

08:16.721 --> 08:17.989
What the hell
does a 9-year-old know

08:18.023 --> 08:19.424
about dealing with change,
yeah?

08:21.459 --> 08:22.894
I'd say a lot.

08:24.596 --> 08:26.898
Yeah.

08:26.932 --> 08:28.800
That's what you said then, too.

08:30.468 --> 08:31.570
What else did I say to you?

08:31.603 --> 08:32.770
Uh, incoming.

08:33.738 --> 08:37.576
It's been really great working
with you, Amy.

08:37.609 --> 08:39.678
I'm so sorry.

08:39.711 --> 08:40.712
Um, where do you want me?

08:40.745 --> 08:42.614
Oh, the fuck out of my studio.

08:42.647 --> 08:45.450
- Uh, sorry?
- Uh, you can sit there.

08:45.483 --> 08:46.585
You know Aaron.

08:46.618 --> 08:48.420
- Hi.
- Yeah.

08:48.453 --> 08:49.988
Uh, 90 seconds, Amy.

08:50.021 --> 08:53.525
You know, I've got to say
it is such an honor

08:53.558 --> 08:57.529
to watch you do your show
tonight.

08:59.064 --> 09:01.733
Uh, are you alright?

09:01.766 --> 09:05.070
- Fuck.
- Jesus, what happened?

09:05.103 --> 09:07.072
Oh.

09:07.105 --> 09:09.040
Oh.

09:10.642 --> 09:12.110
- Jesus!
- Fuck.

09:12.143 --> 09:15.046
Hey, um, if you...
if you need a minute,

09:15.080 --> 09:17.015
I can cover the beginning
of the show.

09:17.048 --> 09:18.750
Yeah, you would love that,
wouldn't you?

09:18.783 --> 09:19.551
What?

09:19.584 --> 09:20.353
Um, no.

09:20.385 --> 09:21.953
I mean I think
you're really bleeding.

09:21.987 --> 09:23.421
- No, I'm fine!
- It's bad.

09:23.455 --> 09:26.558
I'm fine, okay?

09:27.993 --> 09:31.963
And look, I'm just gonna say it,
alright?

09:31.997 --> 09:33.798
You and Bob...

09:36.801 --> 09:38.837
Listen, when I first started
here, okay...

09:38.870 --> 09:39.771
I know.

09:39.804 --> 09:40.672
I didn't realize it then, but...

09:40.705 --> 09:42.240
Look, I know what you're trying
to do, but...

09:42.274 --> 09:44.676
You don't realize it now. You've
got blinders on, that's all I'm saying.

09:44.709 --> 09:46.044
I'm not stupid.

09:46.077 --> 09:47.913
I know you're not stupid,
Miss UC Berkeley.

09:47.946 --> 09:51.783
I'm just trying to give you
some perspective, okay?

09:51.816 --> 09:52.918
Because when I was your age...

09:52.951 --> 09:54.119
My age?

09:54.152 --> 09:56.788
AMY Yes, when I was your
age, I made a lot of mistakes.

09:56.821 --> 09:58.790
And I'm just here to tell you
it's really not worth your while.

09:58.823 --> 10:00.892
Do you honestly think
I'm bangin' Bob?

10:06.831 --> 10:09.000
Look, you may have had to sleep
with him

10:09.034 --> 10:10.535
in order to lock down this job,

10:10.568 --> 10:15.674
but I only had to make him
think that I wanted to.

10:15.707 --> 10:17.542
You are such a little girl.

10:17.575 --> 10:19.044
You really hate that, don't you?

10:19.077 --> 10:20.078
10 seconds, Amy.

10:20.111 --> 10:22.180
You swan into my studio
and don't think you own it.

10:22.213 --> 10:24.516
Here's the tea, Amy.

10:24.549 --> 10:28.019
I am the one who convinced Bob
to give you one last show.

10:28.053 --> 10:28.987
As a courtesy.

10:29.020 --> 10:32.223
I mean, you were really
never my cup of kombucha,

10:32.257 --> 10:36.661
but my parents always really
did have such a soft spot

10:36.695 --> 10:38.096
for you, so...

10:38.129 --> 10:39.664
<i>...at...</i>

10:39.698 --> 10:41.232
- <i>10 Minutes to Midnight.</i>
- You're welcome.

10:44.803 --> 10:45.904
♪ 10 minutes ♪

10:45.937 --> 10:50.008
♪ 10 minutes to midnight ♪

10:51.609 --> 10:52.577
♪ 10 minutes to midnight ♪

10:52.610 --> 10:54.746
And it's 10 Minutes to Midnight.

10:54.779 --> 10:56.081
I'm Amy Marlowe.

10:56.114 --> 10:57.882
Keep breathing, Ames.

10:58.984 --> 10:59.851
You know, storms like this,

10:59.884 --> 11:02.120
they always make me
a little introspective

11:02.153 --> 11:04.289
and I thought tonight
I'd like to bring back

11:04.322 --> 11:07.993
an old favorite, "Ask Amy".

11:08.026 --> 11:09.294
If you're meeting
some challenges,

11:09.328 --> 11:12.130
if you need a little guidance,
give us a call.

11:12.163 --> 11:15.867
509-152-WLST.

11:15.900 --> 11:17.635
Now, before those lines
start lighting up,

11:17.669 --> 11:22.273
I want you to meet my co-host
for the night, Sienna Walters!

11:22.307 --> 11:23.174
Walker, hi.

11:23.208 --> 11:25.944
Sienna is a recent graduate
of UC Berkeley

11:25.977 --> 11:29.647
and she's here to take my job.

11:29.681 --> 11:31.082
Line 1.

11:31.116 --> 11:31.916
Hello, caller.

11:31.950 --> 11:33.618
What's your problem?

11:33.651 --> 11:35.153
<i>Oh, uh, hi.</i>

11:35.186 --> 11:38.189
<i>I... I just dumped my girlfriend,
but...</i>

11:38.223 --> 11:40.125
Aw! CALLER 1:
<i>I'm having second thoughts.</i>

11:40.158 --> 11:41.626
Sounds like it's on you, caller.

11:41.659 --> 11:42.328
<i>What?</i>

11:42.361 --> 11:44.029
- <i>No, lo... look...</i>
- Yeah.

11:44.062 --> 11:45.897
You're having some arguments,
and a dry spell...

11:45.930 --> 11:47.065
<i>Some troubles.</i>

11:47.098 --> 11:48.066
And irreconcilable differences.

11:48.099 --> 11:49.000
<i>We were just arguing.</i>

11:49.034 --> 11:52.871
I tell you what,
let's get Sienna's hot take.

11:52.904 --> 11:53.772
<i>Who?</i>

11:53.805 --> 11:54.672
Come on, speak up.

11:54.706 --> 11:55.774
Use your radio voice.

11:55.807 --> 11:57.709
Uh...

11:57.742 --> 11:59.010
I think I need more details.

11:59.044 --> 12:00.278
I think it's pretty cut and dry.

12:00.311 --> 12:02.147
<i>Come on,
are you serious right now?</i>

12:02.180 --> 12:02.947
Really, caller.

12:02.981 --> 12:05.050
I think
you're overcomplicating things.

12:05.083 --> 12:06.684
Aaron, patch the next one
through.

12:06.718 --> 12:07.685
<i>Wait, wait...</i>

12:07.719 --> 12:09.254
<i>I'm a little nervous.</i>

12:09.287 --> 12:09.888
Oh, don't be nervous.

12:09.921 --> 12:11.956
It's just your old Auntie Amy.

12:11.990 --> 12:13.625
What's your issue?

12:13.658 --> 12:16.928
<i>Well, I've just been
a listener for the longest time, Amy...</i>

12:16.961 --> 12:18.163
And you wanted to call
and tell me

12:18.196 --> 12:20.031
how much the show means to you.

12:20.065 --> 12:21.166
<i>Yeah.</i>

12:21.199 --> 12:22.067
And how your pathetic
little townie life

12:22.100 --> 12:25.003
wouldn't have any significance
without me?

12:25.036 --> 12:25.970
<i>Huh?</i>

12:26.004 --> 12:27.772
- Am I close?
- <i>What?</i>

12:27.806 --> 12:28.673
Next!

12:29.674 --> 12:31.343
You know, caller number 3,
I wanna do something

12:31.377 --> 12:32.411
a little different with you.

12:32.445 --> 12:33.044
- <i>Uh...</i>
- Okay?

12:33.078 --> 12:35.947
I'm gonna ask you the question.

12:35.980 --> 12:37.715
Now, if you had a time machine,

12:37.749 --> 12:39.951
and you could go back
and do it all again, would you?

12:39.984 --> 12:40.819
<i>Well, actually, Amy...</i>

12:40.852 --> 12:43.021
Because I haven't gotten up
with the sun

12:43.054 --> 12:45.690
- for the last 30 years.
- <i>Great.</i>

12:45.723 --> 12:47.959
And what the fuck
has it gotten me?

12:47.992 --> 12:49.794
What's my prize?

12:49.828 --> 12:52.163
I'm sitting
in a dilapidated studio

12:52.197 --> 12:54.366
with Sienna fucking Walker.

12:54.400 --> 12:56.201
I could be your mother!

12:56.234 --> 12:58.903
I mean I was in my 20s when you were
born, for God's sakes!

12:58.937 --> 13:00.406
I wouldn't even have been
a teen mom,

13:00.439 --> 13:01.706
I would've been a real mom!

13:01.739 --> 13:03.041
I... I really think that uh, we...

13:03.074 --> 13:04.343
- You think.
- We could take a break.

13:04.376 --> 13:05.243
I'm glad you think.

13:05.276 --> 13:07.212
It's important you think,
because that means

13:07.245 --> 13:08.880
you're not just legs and tits.

13:08.913 --> 13:09.914
Amy, relax.

13:09.948 --> 13:12.283
That whole idea has
just bathed me in relief.

13:12.317 --> 13:13.151
I don't actually think
that that's...

13:13.184 --> 13:15.253
But you know what?
You're absolutely right.

13:15.286 --> 13:16.154
You're right.

13:16.187 --> 13:19.124
It is not about us,
it is about the caller.

13:19.157 --> 13:21.993
And if there's one takeaway
for you tonight, caller,

13:22.026 --> 13:23.027
it's gonna be this.

13:23.061 --> 13:25.130
