can you get Robert for me?

58:24.996 --> 58:26.097
What?

58:26.131 --> 58:27.032
Robert.

58:27.065 --> 58:28.099
I need him.

58:28.133 --> 58:30.635
Now.

58:30.669 --> 58:32.637
Uh, yeah.

58:32.671 --> 58:33.805
Sure.

58:41.813 --> 58:43.582
Everything alright there, Ames?

58:49.921 --> 58:54.559
When did you know
this was gonna be my last show?

58:54.593 --> 58:56.461
Uh, just...

58:56.494 --> 58:57.929
Give it to me straight.

59:01.066 --> 59:02.367
A week ago.

59:10.976 --> 59:12.110
Thanks.

59:18.783 --> 59:20.752
Kiddo, what's going on?

59:20.785 --> 59:22.754
I'm not gonna
beat around the bush.

59:22.787 --> 59:24.055
This is it.

59:24.089 --> 59:25.123
Last show.

59:25.156 --> 59:25.724
I'm being replaced.

59:25.757 --> 59:27.959
Amy, let's not make a fuss.

59:27.993 --> 59:31.596
We have a nice sunrise
farewell party for you planned.

59:31.630 --> 59:33.498
Red velvet cake.

59:33.531 --> 59:34.566
Yes, your favorite.

59:34.599 --> 59:35.834
My favorite.

59:40.639 --> 59:41.806
Five seconds, Amy.

59:49.681 --> 59:51.750
It's <i>10 Minutes to Midnight.</i>

59:51.783 --> 59:53.084
I'm Amy Marlowe.

59:54.219 --> 59:59.658
Amy, my God, you really stuck
the landing tonight, huh.

59:59.691 --> 01:00:01.893
I knew you had it in you.

01:00:01.927 --> 01:00:05.196
And this... this is all for you.

01:00:24.049 --> 01:00:25.717
Why do you look so depressed?

01:00:33.091 --> 01:00:35.560
You earned this.

01:00:35.593 --> 01:00:36.728
Enjoy.

01:00:52.577 --> 01:00:53.878
Having fun?

01:00:55.814 --> 01:00:59.551
You did great tonight.

01:00:59.584 --> 01:01:01.987
What's wrong?

01:01:02.020 --> 01:01:04.055
I don't know who I am
without this place.

01:01:04.089 --> 01:01:06.057
Uh, Amy.

01:01:06.091 --> 01:01:07.158
Robert.

01:01:09.327 --> 01:01:10.595
Aaron, I just...

01:01:12.964 --> 01:01:15.166
You're leaving a legacy behind.

01:01:15.200 --> 01:01:17.535
Oh bullshit.

01:01:17.569 --> 01:01:19.537
The only thing you ever
leave behind is a headstone

01:01:19.571 --> 01:01:21.806
and you're lucky
if you get that.

01:01:23.041 --> 01:01:25.643
Well, I can't say
I'm not gonna miss you.

01:01:25.677 --> 01:01:27.112
Too little, too late, I know,

01:01:27.145 --> 01:01:30.682
but I always kinda had a crush
on you.

01:01:31.916 --> 01:01:33.184
You ever feel like
you know someone?

01:01:33.218 --> 01:01:36.888
I mean really know them.

01:01:36.921 --> 01:01:39.924
Even if you've never seen them
before?

01:01:44.763 --> 01:01:45.630
Of course, you do.

01:01:45.663 --> 01:01:48.700
Who am I talking to here?

01:01:48.733 --> 01:01:52.270
Ever realize the opposite
is true?

01:01:52.303 --> 01:01:54.606
What do you mean?

01:01:54.639 --> 01:01:57.742
That people aren't
who you think they are.

01:01:57.776 --> 01:01:59.310
That you never really
knew anybody.

01:02:13.359 --> 01:02:14.659
Hmm.

01:02:14.692 --> 01:02:15.860
Hey!

01:02:15.894 --> 01:02:17.595
Alright, everybody!

01:02:17.629 --> 01:02:18.663
It's time for cake!

01:02:18.696 --> 01:02:20.031
Oh yeah!

01:02:20.065 --> 01:02:21.400
Yeah, it's time to cut,
come on...

01:02:21.434 --> 01:02:24.069
<i>We'll keep rolling
into forever as we raise a glass</i>

01:02:24.102 --> 01:02:27.105
<i>to the vintage vixen
of radio land.</i>

01:02:27.138 --> 01:02:30.342
<i>Let's make some noise
and keep the party rolling</i>

01:02:30.376 --> 01:02:32.077
<i>for the lady of the hour</i>

01:02:32.110 --> 01:02:34.946
<i>and her last trip
down the airwaves.</i>

01:02:34.979 --> 01:02:37.248
<i>It's Amy Marlowe, everybody.</i>

01:02:37.282 --> 01:02:41.753
<i>Come on and show her the love
while you still can.</i>

01:02:41.786 --> 01:02:42.821
Oh, there she is.

01:02:42.854 --> 01:02:45.790
Amy, my dear, Amy.

01:02:45.824 --> 01:02:47.125
My golden girl.

01:02:47.158 --> 01:02:50.261
30 years you've been with me!

01:02:50.295 --> 01:02:54.699
30 glorious years.

01:02:54.732 --> 01:02:58.002
And I do declare,
without a shadow of a doubt,

01:02:58.036 --> 01:03:01.106
you have given us
everything you have to give

01:03:01.139 --> 01:03:04.309
and tonight was no exception.

01:03:04.343 --> 01:03:06.978
I mean, what a finale!

01:03:07.011 --> 01:03:08.246
- Am I right?
- Yeah.

01:03:08.279 --> 01:03:09.013
Am I right?

01:03:09.047 --> 01:03:09.981
- That's right?
- Yeah.

01:03:10.014 --> 01:03:15.354
Oh, oh, I remember
the very first day I met you,

01:03:15.387 --> 01:03:17.722
my dear Amy Marlowe.

01:03:17.755 --> 01:03:20.892
She was a shy young thing.

01:03:20.925 --> 01:03:23.429
But we gave you a voice,
and a platform,

01:03:23.462 --> 01:03:28.733
and the rest is,
as the scholars say, history.

01:03:29.667 --> 01:03:34.172
And I have made a career,
as you know, nay...

01:03:34.205 --> 01:03:35.441
SIENNA, ROBERT, AND CROWD:
A life!

01:03:35.474 --> 01:03:36.908
Right!

01:03:36.941 --> 01:03:40.945
Out of seeing things in people.

01:03:40.979 --> 01:03:46.918
And rest assured,
your memory will surely live on.

01:03:46.951 --> 01:03:51.022
Your spirit is entombed
in this building

01:03:51.055 --> 01:03:54.893
for as long as these walls
shall stand.

01:03:54.926 --> 01:03:56.294
To Amy.

01:03:56.327 --> 01:03:57.328
To Amy!

01:03:57.363 --> 01:03:58.229
Yes.

